Six ODM MPs from Nyanza have threatened to mobilise the public to prevent tenants from occupying the Sh4.2 billion Lake Basin Development Authority Mall if the government auctions it.The leaders yesterday alleged there is a plot to auction the mall to &ldquo;powerful people in the Jubilee government&rdquo;.The legislators are Opiyo Wandayi (Ugunja), Fred Outa (Nyando), James Nyikal (Seme), Silvance Osele (Kasipul Kabondo) and woman representatives Christine Ombaka (Siaya) and Rose Nyamunga (Kisumu).Wandayi said the mall risks being grabbed. &ldquo;We will do everything possible to stop any person who might be planning to take this asset,&rdquo; he said. Last week, the government sent a technical team from the department of public works to determine the value of the building.